Date: 6/4/2002
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 6
Edition:
Quote: Lynne King.. quotes the Collins Concise Dictionary in her defence of the strange New Zealand practice of calling school children students instead of pupils... Pupils creep like snails, unwillingly to school, with their satchels, to be taught by teachers, generally at public expense. Students go to university of technical college because they want to. They study under tutors and they pay for the privilege (eventually).
